<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcb012dc5-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s14505"><num value="14505">§ 14505.</num><heading> State tax</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A State or political subdivision thereof may not collect or levy a tax, fee, head charge, or other charge on—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idcb012dc6-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s14505/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> a passenger traveling in interstate commerce by motor carrier;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idcb012dc7-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s14505/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> the transportation of a passenger traveling in interstate commerce by motor carrier;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idcb012dc8-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s14505/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> the sale of passenger transportation in interstate commerce by motor carrier; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idcb012dc9-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s14505/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> the gross receipts derived from such transportation.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idcb012dca-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/104/88/tI/s103">Pub. L. 104–88, title I, § 103</ref>, <date date="1995-12-29">Dec. 29, 1995</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/109/904">109 Stat. 904</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idcb012dcb-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idcb012dcc-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idcb012dcd-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1996-01-01">Jan. 1, 1996</date>, except as otherwise provided in <ref href="/us/pl/104/88">Pub. L. 104–88</ref>, see <ref href="/us/pl/104/88/s2">section 2 of Pub. L. 104–88</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t49/s1301">section 1301 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
